</span></h1><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-1684_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;--s-lg:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-1685_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cZMNgc bNHzPH pf-1686_"><i class="sc-fbyfCU cFdiHx pf-1687_ pfa pfa-book-open-reader" data-pf-type="Icon"></i>Dr Richard Dune</h3><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cZMNgc bNHzPH pf-1688_"><i class="sc-fbyfCU cFdiHx pf-1689_ pfa pfa-calendar-days" data-pf-type="Icon"></i>18-10-2023</h3></div></div></div><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/UK_Malnutrition_Awareness_Week_2023_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1697559418" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/UK_Malnutrition_Awareness_Week_2023_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1697559418 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/UK_Malnutrition_Awareness_Week_2023_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1000x.png?v=1697559418 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/UK_Malnutrition_Awareness_Week_2023_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1697559418 320w" width="1936" height="1352" alt="UK Malnutrition Awareness Week 2023 - The Mandatory Training Group UK -.png__PID:2075e873-3655-495c-92d9-6b58a536ce1d" title="UK Malnutrition Awareness Week 2023 - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-1690_"/></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-a51c" data-category="Generic Content" data-name="Matcha" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-hAcGzb jHOovW pf-1691_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-eGPXGI cIlovf"><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-1692_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-1693_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-1694_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1696_">Unmasking Malnutrition: Join the UK Malnutrition Awareness Week 2023</span></h2><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-1697_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1699_">In a world where the spotlight often lands on global hunger crises, it's easy to forget that malnutrition isn't just a problem reserved for distant shores. It exists, sometimes silently, in our very own backyards.<br><br>From 6th to 12th November 2023, the UK Malnutrition Awareness Week (#UKMAW2023) seeks to pull back the curtain on this issue, revealing its profound impact on our communities, especially among older people.
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-1700_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1702_">A united front against malnutrition
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/A_united_front_against_malnutrition_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1697559580" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/A_united_front_against_malnutrition_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1697559580 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/A_united_front_against_malnutrition_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1697559580 320w" width="1307" height="871" alt="A united front against malnutrition - The Mandatory Training Group UK -.png__PID:c9c28eb9-4a16-48b5-9d17-855219a86530" title="A united front against malnutrition - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-1703_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-1704_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1706_">The Malnutrition Task Force (MTF) and BAPEN are again joining for #UKMAW2023. While the MTF hones in on the plight of older individuals, BAPEN casts its lens on disease-related malnutrition. These two perspectives provide a comprehensive overview of malnutrition's vast expanse.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-1707_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1709_">Why this matters
</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Why_this_matters_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1697559686" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Why_this_matters_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1697559686 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Why_this_matters_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1697559686 320w" width="720" height="480" alt="Why this matters - The Mandatory Training Group UK -.png__PID:872f760d-8a0f-49da-86d0-ad16d0bc4faf" title="Why this matters - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-1710_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-1711_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1713_">Simply put, malnutrition is debilitating. It affects the body and the mind, leading to many health issues, increased hospital stays, and a decreased quality of life. Most alarmingly, it often goes unnoticed until it's too late.
<br><br>Think of your grandparents, neighbours, or even the older woman you pass by every morning on your commute. They might seem fine on the surface, but dig a little deeper, and the cracks begin to show. The loose-fitting clothes, the declining energy levels, or even the empty refrigerator could all be tell-tale signs.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-1714_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1716_">#UKMAW2023: The highlights
</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/UKMAW2023_The_highlights_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1697559812" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/UKMAW2023_The_highlights_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1697559812 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/UKMAW2023_The_highlights_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1697559812 320w" width="1800" height="1200" alt="#UKMAW2023 The highlights - The Mandatory Training Group UK -.png__PID:ed686f9c-58a1-4fb5-8892-c99efb3f998e" title="#UKMAW2023: The highlights - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-1717_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-1718_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1720_">Monday, 6th November: Dive into the Learning Event, be part of BAPEN's MAG National Screening Survey, and remember to nominate your nutrition superheroes. These individuals are champions in the fight against malnutrition, and their efforts deserve to be showcased.
</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-jHkVzv gbyaRg pf-1721_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-1722_"><b>Interactive Tuesday</b> - Share your story. What have you observed? What solutions have you discovered? Use #UKMAW2023 and join a community committed to positive change.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-1724_"><b>Access to good nutrition Wednesday</b> - From Meals on Wheels to home delivery food services, it's a day to celebrate those entities, ensuring everyone has access to nutritious meals.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-1726_"><b>Thirsty Thursday</b> - Hydration is just as crucial. Brainstorm and share creative ways to ensure everyone gets their daily water intake.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-1728_"><b>Robust and resilient Friday</b> - Prepare for winter, know where to get your vaccines, and arm yourself with knowledge and resources to remain healthy.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-1730_"><b>Social media weekend </b>- Cap off the week by celebrating those superheroes in nutrition. The individuals and organisations who go above and beyond every day deserve applause.
</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-1732_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1734_">What can you do?
</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_can_you_do_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1697559930" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_can_you_do_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1697559930 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_can_you_do_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1697559930 320w" width="1463" height="976" alt="What can you do - The Mandatory Training Group UK -.jpg__PID:2b43029d-b857-4b08-94d4-c3b126d9ce12" title="What can you do? - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-1735_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-1736_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1738_">The mantra for #UKMAW2023 is 'Ask, Look, Listen'. It's a simple yet powerful call to action.
<br><br>Ask about appetites and daily struggles.
<br><br>Look for signs of weight loss or difficulties in daily activities.
<br><br>Listen to their concerns, fears, and hopes. Often, these conversations can lead to early interventions, ensuring individuals get the support they need.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-1739_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1741_">A movement born out of need
</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/A_movement_born_out_of_need_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1697560888" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/A_movement_born_out_of_need_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1697560888 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/A_movement_born_out_of_need_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1697560888 320w" width="1490" height="993" alt="A movement born out of need - The Mandatory Training Group UK -.png__PID:e8423943-8be1-4fdf-a0f6-6dac7bd5dfc3" title="A movement born out of need - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-1742_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-1743_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1745_">UKMAW was initiated in 2018 by the combined forces of MTF and BAPEN. It has grown exponentially, shining a light on malnutrition in various sectors. Born in 2012, the Malnutrition Task Force aims to mitigate preventable malnutrition in older people. Their tireless efforts have sparked conversations, leading to tangible change in communities.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-1746_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1748_">Join the fight
</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Join_the_fight_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_661c64be-8a68-4cb6-b449-e6b4ead60a9a.png?v=1697618217" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Join_the_fight_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_661c64be-8a68-4cb6-b449-e6b4ead60a9a.png?v=1697618217 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Join_the_fight_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_661c64be-8a68-4cb6-b449-e6b4ead60a9a_500x.png?v=1697618217 320w" width="1440" height="960" alt="Join the fight - The Mandatory Training Group UK -.png__PID:0abaabe1-9212-4a47-8ac7-6e917dc9cee8" title="Join the fight - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-1749_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-1750_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1752_">As we approach #UKMAW2023, it's a call to arms for every individual. You don't need to be a health professional or a nutrition expert. All it takes is a keen eye, an open heart, and a commitment to making a difference.
<br><br>Remember, malnutrition is preventable. It begins with awareness, followed by action. Let's make this year's UK Malnutrition Awareness Week a milestone towards a nourished and thriving community.
<br><br>Stay updated. Engage in the conversations. Be part of the change.
